entry.title: Fix bisect-builds.py to work with ASan builds.
entry.content:
- Add a `/` to the prefix when enumerating ASan build: this speeds up

enumeration of linux-release builds by avoiding useless enumeration of

linux-release-chromeos and linux-release-v8-arm builds.

- Use the correct archive name for Linux: after r398598, the ASan base

path on Linux matches other platforms. No attempt is made to handle

the legacy archive name, as r398598 is nearly 8 years old at this

point.

- Handle handle zip archives when a entry's file name has no directory

component. os.path.dirname('only_filename') returns an empty string,

and trying to make a directory with no name fails.

- Unzip ASan archive into a subdirectory rather than directly into the

temp directory, as that is what the rest of the script expects.

- Remove the custom result evaluator for ASan since ASan builds may

encounter safety violations unrelated to the bug being evaluated

Instead, have the script print out any detected ASan errors to stdout

and allow the user to make a manual determination.

entry.title: Audio: Preload MediaFoundation audio decoder library in Gpu process
entry.content:
Dolby's audio decoder for AC3,EC3 will be provided on windows as codec

package in next windows release, and libraries in those codec packages

will be signed by Dolby's certificate only. But

MediaFoundationAudioDecoder in chromium can initialize decoder library

with Microsoft signature only in sandboxed GPU process.



Dolby's library can not be signed by Microsoft, so we need a walkaround

to fix this problem.



Chromium GPU process is allowed to load some .dll files before it be

sandboxed. So we can load Dolby's library from MediaFoundation codec

package in that time.



And this problem is exist for other audio/video codecs too, they can add a little code to support their codecs.



BTW, this solution is from Microsoft.

entry.content:
This CL introduces common types for tabs and tab groups

to be compatible in crossplatform layer.

Specifically,

1. It uses LocalTabID for local tab ID which

is base::Token, int or string on different platforms.

2. It uses LocalTabGroupID for local tab group ID

which is tab_groups::TabGroupID or int or base::Token

on different platforms.

3. Only //components/saved_tab_groups layer was touched.

//chrome layer was left unchanged.

creating a SavedTabGroup.

entry.title: Propagate "extract zip file" errors on Clippy
entry.content:
- Prior to this commit, if there's a zipped file on Microsoft

OneDrive and you right-click, then choose Extract all: it

should fail. This failure isn't shown in the Files App UI.

What actually happens is that the error isn't properly handled

and the preparing panel in the Files app doesn't change

because the error wasn't propagated.



- ExtractIOTask::ExtractIntoNewDirectory mistakenly only goes

on to ExtractIOTask::FinishedExtraction (and its decrement of "the number of outstanding extractions" count) in the

success case. In the failure case, Complete never gets called.



- This CL changes ExtractIOTask to propagate the error to the Files

app when it fails to create new directory.

entry.content:
The request fd acts as a fence for the completion of

the OUTPUT, CAPTURE, and MEDIA_REQUEST queues. This avoids

looping on dequeuing each buffer individually.



This change reduces the independence of the queues and

that is desirable. There may be a very small performance

boost by continuing when the OUTPUT queue has returned.

In reality all of the queues complete at the same time.

entry.title: Switch path validation to use win32 path
entry.content:
This CL changes the data format for the validation data to use

buffers instead of strings. In order to pass the data back over

COM however, a translation is done between buffer and string.



Since buffers are being used, the data format is changed to use

a single byte to indicate the validation type, followed by

the validation data itself.



Path validation is also changed to use win32 paths instead of

native paths, to ensure that if volume identifiers change, the

validation data remains stable.



In addition, all code is changed to use (native) std::wstring

and base::FilePath to make any file path parsing easier to

reason about.



A new test is added to verify the `TrimProcessPath` function,

however existing tests can remain the same and verify that

the functionality before and after is identical.



BUG=41493095
